{
  "page": "Durran Godsgrief",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">\"Durran\" redirects here. For the Unsullied, see <a href=\"/index.php/Duran\" title=\"Duran\">Duran</a>. For others with the same name, see <a href=\"/index.php/Durran_(disambiguation)\" title=\"Durran (disambiguation)\">Durran (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\"><img alt=\"House Baratheon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/2d/House_Baratheon.svg/50px-House_Baratheon.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/2d/House_Baratheon.svg/75px-House_Baratheon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/2d/House_Baratheon.svg/100px-House_Baratheon.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> King</span><br />Durran Godsgrief</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\"><img alt=\"House Baratheon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/2d/House_Baratheon.svg/50px-House_Baratheon.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/2d/House_Baratheon.svg/75px-House_Baratheon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/2d/House_Baratheon.svg/100px-House_Baratheon.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Durran_Elenei.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Durran Elenei.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/57/Durran_Elenei.jpg/316px-Durran_Elenei.jpg\" width=\"316\" height=\"560\" srcset=\"/images/5/57/Durran_Elenei.jpg 1.5x\" /></a><div>Durran and his wife <a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a>, from <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <i>Histories &amp; Lore</i> © HBO</div></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Monarch</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Full name</th><td>\nDurran</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm King</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Heir</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Durran_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran II Durrandon\">Durran the Devout</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Successor</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Durran_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran II Durrandon\">Durran the Devout</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Personal Information</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Durran Godsgrief</li><li>The Godsgrief</li><li>King of a Thousand Years</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">Family</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Dynasty</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Queen</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Durran_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran II Durrandon\">Durran the Devout</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;\">References</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Durran</b>, called <b>Durran Godsgrief</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and <b>the Godsgrief</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> was the mythic first <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm King</a> and the founder of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a>. Legend has that he was married to <a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a> and was the builder of <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#The_Winds_of_Winter\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Character\">Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Durran\" title=\"Category:Images of Durran\">Images of Durran</a></div>\n<p>Durran was unrelenting<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and defiant.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/23/Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg/350px-Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg\" width=\"350\" height=\"241\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/23/Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg/525px-Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/23/Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg/700px-Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Durran_and_Elenei.jpeg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a> protects Durran as his castle is destroyed by her parents. Art by Roman Papsuev ©</div></div></div>\n<p>According to legend, in the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a>, Durran won the love of <a href=\"/index.php/Elenei\" title=\"Elenei\">Elenei</a>, the daughter of the <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_god\" title=\"Sea god\">sea god</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Goddess_of_the_wind\" title=\"Goddess of the wind\">goddess of the wind</a>. Her divine parents forbade their love, but Durran and Elenei wed despite them. When she gave her <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenhead\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maidenhead\">maidenhead</a> to him on their wedding night, committing herself to a mortal life, the gods' wrath was terrible to behold. They destroyed Durran's keep, killing all his family and the wedding guests, but Elenei protected Durran from the storm. Enraged, Durran declared war on the gods, who replied by hammering his kingdom with massive storms. Each time Durran built a castle to face the sea, the gods destroyed it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>King Durran's lords pleaded with him to build inland, his priests told him he must placate the gods by giving Elenei back to the sea, and even his <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> begged him to relent. But Durran refused, and persisted building larger and more powerful fortifications. Finally, the seventh castle stayed in place at <a href=\"/index.php/Durran%27s_Point\" title=\"Durran&#39;s Point\">Durran's Point</a> and resisted the storms of <a href=\"/index.php/Shipbreaker_Bay\" title=\"Shipbreaker Bay\">Shipbreaker Bay</a>. Some believe this is because the <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a> took a hand in its construction, shaping the stones with <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">magic</a>. Others believe that a young boy, who grew up to be <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_the_Builder\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bran the Builder\">Bran the Builder</a>, advised Durran on its construction. The truth of the matter is unknown. Nevertheless, <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> resisted everything the gods threw at it, and Durran reigned with Elenei at his side for a thousand years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Storm's End has been called Durran's Defiance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Though Durran supposedly ruled for a thousand years, Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Glaive\" title=\"Glaive\">Glaive</a> proposed that the \"King of a Thousand Years\" was in fact a succession of monarchs all bearing the same name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_Kings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Storm Kings\">Storm Kings</a> of old from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a> named their firstborn son and heir after Durran Godsgrief, complicating the research of <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">maesters</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Durran Godsgrief claimed the <a href=\"/index.php/Rainwood\" title=\"Rainwood\">rainwood</a>, but much of it was returned to the children of the forest by his son, <a href=\"/index.php/Durran_II_Durrandon\" title=\"Durran II Durrandon\">Durran the Devout</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_house_durrandon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> arrives at the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">siege of Storm's End</a>, she recalls the legend of Durran and Elenei.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Winds_of_Winter\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Winds of Winter\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #f28500;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Content.png\" src=\"/images/c/cc/Content.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Warning</b> <br /> This information has thus far been released in a sample chapter for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, and might therefore not be in finalized form. Keep in mind that the content as described below is still subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a> recalls her father, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Doran_Martell\" title=\"Doran Martell\">Doran</a>, and Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Caleotte\" title=\"Caleotte\">Caleotte</a> arguing with a <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">septon</a> about why the north and south sides of the <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_of_Dorne\" title=\"Sea of Dorne\">Sea of Dorne</a> were so different. Prince Doran Martell and his <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> favored weather patterns, the way the big storms that formed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a> would pick up moisture until they crashed into <a href=\"/index.php/Cape_Wrath\" title=\"Cape Wrath\">Cape Wrath</a>, though Doran thought it was odd that the storms never struck at <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>. The septon believed the reason was because Durran Godsgrief stole Elenei from her godly parents and earned their eternal enmity, while no Dornishman ever did so.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Names such as <a href=\"/index.php/Brandon_the_Builder\" title=\"Brandon the Builder\">Brandon the Builder</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Garth_Greenhand\" title=\"Garth Greenhand\">Garth Greenhand</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lann_the_Clever\" title=\"Lann the Clever\">Lann the Clever</a>, and Durran Godsgrief are names to conjure with, but it is likely that their legends hold less truth than fancy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Durran_Godsgrief&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=